name: Florentine Bar & Restaurant.

reviews.review_text: Famous for their chicken cafreal. It was really good. we tried the Mixed fried rice, Chicken cafreal & Chicken xacutti. The food tasted good. The quantity was good. The atmosphere is ok. Also we have tried one Pinacolada cocktail, which tasted good. Their service is good, but a bit slow. Parking space is very limited. A small approach road leads to the restaurant.

Worst service. We go there around 10:30 at night, and the waiter on the first floor was complaining it is almost time for closing and asked us why we came at that time. We just ordered chicken cafreal, and four buns. He said they only have two and we agreed. Later another waiter came and throw 2 more buns to the basket like he gave for free. And he ask us to order drinks and we denied. Then he ask to my face, "why you come here just for this. No body comes here just for cafreal, you just wasted your time and our time." and he also commented how fast we finished our food. Worst experience ever in Goa.
A great authentic cozy very goa like ambience...good soul food...mus try and a favorite since years loved by locals is the chicken cafreal...the fry wet bombil and prawns chilly fry was yum...

description:
### Welcome to Florentine Bar & Restaurant

Nestled within the bustling Corlim Industrial Estate, **Florentine Bar & Restaurant** shines brightly with an impressive **4.2-star rating** garnered from **3,076 reviews**. This charming eatery has carved a niche for itself, particularly celebrated for its **chicken cafreal**—a delicious dish that has resonated with patrons, earning it a remarkable **507 mentions**. Other noteworthy dishes, albeit less frequently highlighted, include the aromatic **xacuti**, local bread known as **poi**, and the sweet indulgence of **serradura**.

### Ambiance & Design

Stepping into Florentine, guests are greeted by an authentic Goan vibe, encapsulated in a cozy interior that exudes warmth and charm. The décor reflects a blend of traditional and contemporary elements, fostering a relaxed atmosphere where locals often gather. Customer reviews praise the "good soul food" vibe, enhanced by the subtle background music that complements the inviting setting. For travelers looking for a slice of local culture, this ambiance adds to the experience, marked by friendly faces and hearty conversations.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

At the heart of the culinary offerings is the celebrated **chicken cafreal**, revered for its rich flavors and tender execution. Customers rave about this dish, often pairing it with **Mixed Fried Rice** or indulging in a variety of other seafood delicacies, such as **bombil fry** and **prawns chilly fry**. The **presentation** of the food is both rustic and appetizing, inviting diners to relish each flavor-packed bite. For those seeking variety, dishes like **xacuti** hint at a robust masala richness, while the availability of **poi** provides a delightful touch of Goan tradition.

### Customer Experience & Service

While many reviews celebrate delightful food, service experiences have varied significantly. Some guests have reported exemplary food quality paired with dedicated staff members, though other feedback highlights **concerns about service efficiency**—with one customer describing a particularly disappointing encounter late in the evening where the staff appeared rushed and dismissive. Parking can also be a challenge, with limited space and a narrow access road noted by visitors, suggesting that a little patience may be required when planning your visit.

### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz around Florentine is palpable, with many locals considering it a must-visit spot. Regular patrons and newcomers alike echo sentiments, praising its authentic flavors while occasionally candidly critiquing service delays. Social media chatter reveals a blend of enthusiasm for the standout dishes like **chicken cafreal** while also voicing the need for more attentive service during peak hours. Although no notable decorations or critic ratings have been mentioned, the strong local endorsement is a testament to its appeal.

### Capturing the Essence in Visuals

The provided customer images encapsulate the essence of dining at Florentine. Plates overflowing with vibrant dishes, cozy seat arrangements framed by soft lighting, and the cheerful gathering of diners all paint a vivid picture of what to expect. For instance, one image captures the golden-brown **bombil fry**, its crispy texture inviting immediate indulgence, while another shows a warm **bowl of chicken xacuti**, rich in spices and color. Each photo reflects the lively spirit and delightful offerings that characterize this beloved establishment.

In summary, **Florentine Bar & Restaurant** stands as a cherished culinary destination, particularly for lovers of Goan cuisine. It marries an inviting ambiance with standout dishes that have won the hearts of thousands, all while navigating the ebb and flow of dining experiences that come with a popular location. Whether you're a local or a traveler, consider stopping by for a taste of their famous chicken cafreal—you just might find your new favorite dish.
